&quot;  The first Norton logo was a fairly simple, art nouveau design, with the name spelled in capitals.[as here] However, a new logo appeared on the front of the catalogue for 1914, which was a joint effort by James Lansdowne Norton and his daughter Ethel. It became known as the &quot;curly N&quot; logo, with only the initial letter as a capital, and was used by the company thereafter, first appearing on actual motorcycles in 1915.  &quot;  
